OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 3 Mar to Thu 12 Mar
OL,6,FMuch of this period looks like being
OL,7,Flargely dominated by high pressure,
OL,8,Fespecially towards the south or
OL,9,Fsoutheast of the UK. This will mean
OL,10,Fmany places seeing plenty of dry
OL,11,Fweather with variable cloud amounts
OL,12,Fand some sunshine, the best of this
OL,13,Ftowards the south or southeast, but
OL,14,Fperhaps with some fog overnight.
OL,15,FHowever, frontal systems are still
OL,16,Flikely to affect the north and west of
OL,17,Fthe UK at times though, maybe also
OL,18,Fbriefly affecting other parts,
OL,19,Fbringing some rain and strong winds,
OL,20,Fand perhaps a little snow to the high
OL,21,Fground in the north. Temperatures will
OL,22,Fbe near or above normal, although
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fpatchy overnight frost is still likely
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fat times.
